Los Angeles car parts company to invest in Hungary 
The Los Angeles-based Superior car component factory wants to invest
100 million German marks (some 70 million dollars) in an aluminium
alloy wheel factory in the central town of Tatabanya, an Industrial
Ministry official said here Monday.
The investment would be Superior's fully-owned subsidiary, state
secretary Imre Dunai said.
Construction work is to start this year and trial production is planned
for the first half of 1996.
When the venture runs at full capacity, planned from the second half of
next year, it wo!! turn out two million aluminium car wheels a year
worth 150 million German marks (105 million dollars), Dunai said.
Superior is a supplier to BMW and Mercedes.
